                  "title": "User Identity Spoofing",
                  "status": "Mitigated",
                  "severity": "High",
                  "type": "Spoofing",
                  "description": "An attacker could impersonate a legitimate user by stealing or guessing their credentials, or by hijacking an active session.escription for this threat.",
                  "mitigation": "Passwords are hashed with BCrypt before storage; Rails 8 native rate_limit throttles repeated login attempts (10 requests / 3 minutes) on SessionsController#create; session cookies are signed, httponly, and same_site: lax to prevent tampering and CSRF/XSS-based theft.",
