                  "severity": "Medium",
                  "type": "Repudiation",
                  "description": "A user could deny having performed a sensitive action, making it difficult to establish accountability.",
                  "mitigation": "Sensitive actions are logged server-side with timestamps and tied to the authenticated session, creating an audit trail that supports non-repudiation.",
